    • Method Detail

      • getItemPrice

        int getItemPrice​(int itemID)
        Fetches the Grand Exchange price for a given item ID from the OSRS price API.
        Parameters:
        itemID - the ID of the item to fetch the price for.
        Returns:
        the latest high price if available, otherwise the low price. Returns -1 if both prices are unavailable or in case of an error.

      • isOpen

        boolean isOpen()
        Checks if the Grand Exchange interface is currently open.
        Returns:
        a true/false statement if the Grand Exchange is open or not.

      • getSlotProgress

        int getSlotProgress​(int slot)
        Checks how far your buy/sell offer is within the Grand Exchange.
        Parameters:
        slot - the slot number (1-8) of the slot you'd like to check the sale/buy progress for
        Returns:
        an integer representing the % progress of your buy/sale progress. E.G. 50 would mean it's 50% processed.

      • getCanceled

        int getCanceled()
        Checks the number of canceled orders within the Grand Exchange
        Returns:
        an integer representing the number of canceled orders.

      • getCompleted

        int getCompleted()
        Checks the number of completed orders within the Grand Exchange
        Returns:
        an integer representing the number of completed orders.

      • collectAllItems

        void collectAllItems()
        Checks if there are items to collect, if so it taps the collect button to collect all collectable orders.

      • hasCollectableItems

        boolean hasCollectableItems()
        Checks if there are items to be collected in the Grand Exchange
        Returns:
        a true/false statement if the Grand Exchange has items to collect or not.

      • buyItem

        int buyItem​(java.lang.String searchString,
            int itemID,
            int quantity,
            int price)
        Buys one or more items in the Grand Exchange
        Parameters:
        searchString - The string (item name) to search for, make sure the string ensures you desired item is in the top results (visible without scrolling)
        itemID - The itemID of the item you'd like to buy, use /ID in Discord to find your IDs.
        quantity - The quantity (amount) you'd like to buy of the item.
        price - The price you want to buy the items at.
        Returns:
        an integer representing slot number your buy order is created in. A -1 return means something failed, or no slots are available.

      • sellItem

        int sellItem​(int itemID,
             int quantity,
             int price)
        Sells one or more items in the Grand Exchange
        Parameters:
        itemID - The itemID of the item you'd like to sell, use /ID in Discord to find your IDs.
        quantity - The quantity (amount) you'd like to sell of the item.
        price - The price you want to sell the items at.
        Returns:
        an integer representing slot number your sell order is created in. A -1 return means something failed, or no slots are available.

      • getFirstAvailableSlot

        int getFirstAvailableSlot()
        Checks for the first available slot in the Grand Exchange interface
        Returns:
        an integer representing the slot number of the first available GE slot. A -1 return means no slots are available, or the correct interface is not open.

      • isSlotAvailable

        boolean isSlotAvailable​(int slot)
        Checks if a specific slot is available/empty in the Grand Exchange interface
        Parameters:
        slot - an integer representing the slot you'd like to check (1-8)
        Returns:
        a true/false statement if the Grand Exchange slot is available/empty or not.

      • slotsAvailable

        int slotsAvailable()
        Checks the number of slots available/empty in the Grand Exchange interface
        Returns:
        an integer representing the slot numbers available in the GE. A -1 return means no slots are available, or the correct interface is not open.

      • has1stItemToCollect

        boolean has1stItemToCollect()
        Checks if there is an item to collect inside a slot, specifically the first collect slot of the GE slot. This method is only to be used when a slot is already open!
        Returns:
        a true/false statement if there is an item to be collected or not.

      • has2ndItemToCollect

        boolean has2ndItemToCollect()
        Checks if there is an item to collect inside a slot, specifically the second collect slot of the GE slot. This method is only to be used when a slot is already open!
        Returns:
        a true/false statement if there is an item to be collected or not.
